Named for the Cantonese, 同步, for "to synchronise."

This is mostly a personal tool. Don't expect it to
work well.

You need to have mDNS configured on all the devices.

Run `make install` to install in /usr/bin.

Configuration is stored in /etc/tungbou.conf, but you
can override this location with `--config=/path/`. See
./tungbou.sample.conf for an example config.
